SCIENTIFIC.NAME: Terpsiphone paradisi
SPECIES.COMMENTS: Female (part of mixed flock: 2 Cinereous Tits, 2 Red-whiskered Bulbuls, 4-5 Pale-billed Flowerpeckers, 3 Purple-rumped and 2 Purple Sunbirds, 2 Common Ioras, 1 Female Ind Paradise-Flycatcher, Several Yellow-billed Babblers around, 1 Rose-ringed Parakeet on top. All this on a Cassia Fistula near Veg Garden-side path to Percolation tank bund and very likely alarm calls/heightened vigilance against a raptor (perhaps a Shikra that flew-through. --Later heard in song. Unsure as to whether this was any other flycatcher. Tickell's Blue-like song heard from around where female was seen.
